# One line ending everywhere. Git's Windows default rewrites text to CRLF on checkout,
# so a served asset arrived with \r\n on the Windows CI runner and every test that
# matches a multi-line string in one failed — on a difference nobody wrote. Pinning the
# working tree to LF makes both desks, both runners, and the repo agree.
* text=auto eol=lf

# cmd.exe and PowerShell are the readers that want CRLF.
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.ps1 text eol=crlf
